        "dt": "07 July 2026",
        "qt": "The following are three equivalent conditions for a subgroup H of a group G to be a normal subgroup of G: 1. ghg-1∊H for all g∊G and h∊H. 2. gHg-1=H for all g∊G. 3. gH=Hg for all g∊G.",
